# Cross-Platform Launcher Parity

When editing Linux launcher scripts (especially `tools/run-*.sh` and `resources/linux/launch.sh`), keep equivalent behavior aligned for packaged launchers on all supported platforms when applicable.

Required parity checklist:
- Mirror bridge/runtime behavior changes to `resources/linux/launch.sh` (AppImage runtime).
- Mirror applicable bridge/runtime changes to `resources/macos/launcher`.
- Mirror applicable bridge/runtime changes to `resources/windows/launch.bat`.
- Keep shared defaults/config synchronized in `resources/common/.env.example` and `resources/common/dosbox.conf` when behavior depends on env/config.
- If a change is platform-specific and cannot be mirrored, document the reason in the implementation summary.

Do not ship Linux-only launcher behavior by default if the same behavior is expected cross-platform.
